=H= Information

=h= Registers

Use ‹:reg ›to list registers.

Register types:

‹"       ›      Any text yanked or deleted without specifying another register automatically goes here
‹0       ›      Yanked text
‹1-9     ›      Deleted text (1 is the most recent, and so on)
‹A-Z a-z ›      General-purpose
                      - Using a lowercase letter (e.g., "ay) replaces the content,
                      - while an uppercase letter (e.g., "Ay) appends to it.

‹*       ›      Primary selection (X11)
‹+       ›      System clipboard

‹:       ›      Last executed command (read-only)
‹%       ›      Name of the current file (read-only)

